CTSBS Age-Mixing

Roxanne Beauclair

11 April 2017


Before conducting imputations, I excluded participants who said their sexual preferences were for “both” genders or the same gender (n = 78). I further excluded people who did not identify as black or coloured (n = 7) and people who did not report partners in the previous year (n = 170). Missing observations on those characteristics were left in the dataset. This left 1072 relationships reported by 646 participants. Then I imputed 50 datasets using the random forest method for continuous and nominal categorical variables and the “polr” method for our ordinal variables.


The expected difference in log count of bridgewidth between those HIV positive and those HIV negative. The expected log count of bw for those with HIV is XX higher than those who are negative.
